best deck I&#39;ve seen all day!<br>
<br>
though if you are using gates to the dead city, you might want to play twilight nazgul, as just for spoting one you can add a burden, thus making them have to exert thier companions, and then you can kill one off easier and draw to their power to exhaust all the other companions! so:<br>
IN: It wants to be found x4<br>
IN: Nelya Twilight x2<br>
IN: Blade Tip x2, Ostea Twilight x2<br>
(each time blade tip adds a burden to the ring bearer at start of turn, he has to exert his companion for each gate of the dead city you have!!)<br>
<br>
OUT: Nelya non-twilight x2<br>
OUT: Morgul Skiller x1, Witch King x1, Cantea x1<br>
I dunno what else you want to take out, but you might just want to go with Ostea/Bladetip combo, and twilight nazguls!<br>
<br>
